"title": "2018: Jesus Christ, divinity of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2018: jesus christ, divinity of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The equality and identity of Jesus Christ as God is clearly stated in the NT, and is also implied by the words and deeds of Jesus Christ. The OT prophecies also point to the divinity of the coming Messiah.</p>\n<h2>The NT writers affirm Jesus Christ's divinity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:8\">HEB 1:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:6\">PSA 45:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:1-John1:2\">JHN 1:1–1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:18\">JHN 1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:5\">ROM 9:5</a> <em>NIV footnote has alternative translations: “Christ who is over all. God be for ever praised!” Or: “Christ. God who is over all be for ever praised!”</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:6\">PHP 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:13\">TIT 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:1\">2PE 1:1</a></p>\n<h2>Statements which imply Jesus Christ's divinity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:23\">MAT 1:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:14\">ISA 7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:35\">LUK 1:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:15\">COL 1:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:2\">COL 2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:9\">COL 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:17\">1TI 1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:20\">1JN 5:20</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's unity with the Father and the Holy Spirit in the Godhead</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19\">MAT 28:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:16\">JHN 14:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor13:14\">2CO 13:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:13-Eph1:14\">EPH 1:13–1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:18\">EPH 2:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:22\">EPH 2:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:14-Eph3:17\">EPH 3:14–3:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:4-Eph4:6\">EPH 4:4–4:6</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's eternal nature indicates his divinity</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ precedes creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:17\">COL 1:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic5:2\">MIC 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:5\">JHN 17:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:24\">JHN 17:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:9\">2TI 1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:20\">1PE 1:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:1\">1JN 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:13\">1JN 2:13</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is everlasting</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:58\">JHN 8:58</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:12\">HEB 1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:27\">PSA 102:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:3\">HEB 7:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:24\">HEB 7:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:8\">HEB 13:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:8\">REV 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:13\">REV 5:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:13\">REV 22:13</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's pre-existence indicates his divinity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:62\">JHN 6:62</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:13\">JHN 3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:31\">JHN 3:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:41-John6:42\">JHN 6:41–6:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:3\">JHN 13:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:28\">JHN 16:28</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's manifestation of God's glory indicates his divinity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:3\">HEB 1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:2\">MAT 17:2</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:2-Mark9:3\">MRK 9:2–9:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:29\">LUK 9:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:14\">JHN 1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:8\">1CO 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:4\">2CO 4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:1\">JAS 2:1</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's divinity in the OT</h2>\n<h3>The divinity of the coming Messiah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:6\">ISA 9:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:3\">ISA 40:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:6\">JER 23:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:1\">MAL 3:1</a></p>\n<h3>NT passages which apply OT passages about God to Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:13\">ROM 10:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:32\">JOL 2:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:40-John12:41\">JHN 12:40–12:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:10\">ISA 6:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:33\">ROM 9:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:14\">ISA 8:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:8\">EPH 4:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:18\">PSA 68:18</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's claims to divinity</h2>\n<h3>He claimed to be one with the Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:17-John5:18\">JHN 5:17–5:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:30-John10:33\">JHN 10:30–10:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:36-John10:38\">JHN 10:36–10:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:45\">JHN 12:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:7\">JHN 14:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:9-John14:11\">JHN 14:9–14:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:11\">JHN 17:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:21\">JHN 17:21</a></p>\n<h3>He demonstrated his authority to forgive sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:20-Luke5:24\">LUK 5:20–5:24</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:2-Matt9:6\">MAT 9:2–9:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:5-Mark2:10\">MRK 2:5–2:10</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:47-Luke7:48\">LUK 7:47–7:48</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's actions imply his divinity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:26-Matt8:27\">MAT 8:26–8:27</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:39-Mark4:41\">MRK 4:39–4:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:24-Luke8:25\">LUK 8:24–8:25</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:8\">MAT 12:8</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:28\">MRK 2:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:5\">LUK 6:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:39\">LUK 8:39</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:19-Mark5:20\">MRK 5:19–5:20</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's resurrection confirms his divinity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:36\">ACT 2:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:4\">ROM 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:9-Phil2:11\">PHP 2:9–2:11</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's names and titles point to his divinity</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ as judge</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:27\">JHN 5:27</a></strong> <em>In the OT, final responsibility for judgment is assigned to God.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:31-Matt25:33\">MAT 25:31–25:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:38\">MRK 8:38</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:27\">MAT 16:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:26\">LUK 9:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:31\">ACT 17:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:16\">ROM 2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:10\">2CO 5:10</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ as ``I am''</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:25\">JHN 11:25</a></strong> <em>“I am” is the meaning of God's name in the OT (see <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:14\">Ex 3:14</a>).</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:35\">JHN 6:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:12\">JHN 8:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:7\">JHN 10:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:11\">JHN 10:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:6\">JHN 14:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:1\">JHN 15:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:5-John18:6\">JHN 18:5–18:6</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ as Saviour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:31\">ACT 5:31</a></strong> <em>According to the OT, God alone can save.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:12\">ACT 4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:23\">EPH 5:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:25\">HEB 7:25</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ as Lord</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:9\">ROM 10:9</a></strong> <em>“Lord” was equivalent to God's name in the OT.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:43\">LUK 1:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:11\">LUK 2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:13\">JHN 13:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:3\">1CO 12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:5\">2CO 4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:16\">REV 19:16</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ as creator</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:16\">COL 1:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:3\">JHN 1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:10\">JHN 1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:15\">ACT 3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:36\">ROM 11:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:6\">1CO 8:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:2\">HEB 1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:10\">HEB 1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:25\">PSA 102:25</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ as shepherd</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:20\">HEB 13:20</a></strong> <em>“Shepherd” was a well-known OT name for God.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:11-John10:16\">JHN 10:11–10:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:25\">1PE 2:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:4\">1PE 5:4</a></p>\n<h2>Those who recognised Jesus Christ's divinity</h2>\n<h3>The disciples</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:28\">JHN 20:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:16\">MAT 16:16</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:29\">MRK 8:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:20\">LUK 9:20</a></p>\n<h3>The demons</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:11\">MRK 3:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:41\">LUK 4:41</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:34\">MRK 1:34</a></p>\n<h2>The consequences of recognising Jesus Christ's divinity</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is worshipped as God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:52\">LUK 24:52</a></strong> <em>The fact that no-one but God may be worshipped is fundamental to Judaism.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:11\">MAT 2:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:9\">MAT 28:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:17\">MAT 28:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:38\">JHN 9:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:18\">2TI 4:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:18\">2PE 3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:5-Rev1:6\">REV 1:5–1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:12-Rev5:13\">REV 5:12–5:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:10\">REV 7:10</a></p>\n<h3>Prayer is addressed to Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:59-Acts7:60\">ACT 7:59–7:60</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:13\">ACT 9:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:22\">1CO 16:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:20\">REV 22:20</a></p>",
